    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Condition where a surface or material has cracked due to pressure, differential in temperature, or other strain of some kind. An example is in glassmaking, where fissures develop in the body of a vessel caused by internal strain resulting from inadequate annealing and/or accidental thermal shock.</Note_Text>
